  "texts": [
    "The upsampled representations of all parallel convolutions are mixed to create the output feature maps.",
    "The HRNet transforms a 299 × 299 × 3 face into a 64 × 56 × 56 output shape by passing it through two 3 × 3 convolutions with a stride of size 2.",
    "It is divided into phases, each of which is a subnetwork with several parallel branches.",
    "Every branch has half the resolution and twice the number of channels as the one before it; for example, if the last branch's resolution is C, the first branch's network resolutions are 8C, 4C, 2C, and C. Two residual blocks, each with two 3 × 3 convolutions, make up one branch.The first phase is to generate a 16 × 56 × 56 feature vector with a high-resolution subnet comprising one residual block with four distinct size convolutions.",
    "The next three steps add high-to-low-resolution subnetworks one at a time."
  ],
